==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Integument
<hw>In*teg"u*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>integumentum</ets>, fr. <ets>integere</ets> to cover; pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in, on + <ets>tegere</ets> to cover: cf. F.
<ets>int⟦eacute⟧gument</ets>. See 1st <er>n-</er>, and
<er>Tegument</er>.]</ety> <def>That which naturally invests or covers
another thing, as the testa or the tegmen of a seed; specifically
<fld>(Anat.)</fld>, a covering which invests the body, as the skin, or a
membrane that invests a particular part.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Integumentary</ent>⟦br⟧
